text_retweet:
#repost @ibizoboi
・・・
1 more month until the release of black enough: stories of being young & black in america! 1.8.19
#
⭐️”editor zoboi (pride, 2018, etc.) lays out the collection’s purpose: exploring black interconnectedness, traditions, and identity in terms of how they apply to black teens. given that scope, that most stories are contemporary realistic fiction makes sense (rita williams-garcia’s humorous “whoa!” which dips into the waters of speculative fiction, is a notable exception). conversely, the characters are incredibly varied, as are the narrative styles. standouts include the elegant simplicity of jason reynolds’ “the ingredients,” about a group of boys walking home from the swimming pool; leah henderson’s “warning: color may fade,” about an artist afraid to express herself; the immediacy of tracey baptiste’s “gravity,” about a #metoo moment of self-actualization birthed from violation; renee watson’s reflection on family in “half a moon”; and the collection’s namesake, varian johnson’s “black enough,” which highlights the paradigm shift that is getting woke. in these stories, black kids are nerds and geeks, gay and lesbian, first gen and immigrants, outdoorsy and artists, conflicted and confused, grieving and succeeding, thriving and surviving—in short, they’re fully human. no collection could represent the entire spectrum of blackness, however, the presence of trans, afro-latinx, and physically disabled characters is missed: a clarion call for more authentic black-centric collections.

a breath of fresh air and a sigh of long overdue relief. nuanced and necessary.” (kirkus reviews (starred review))#bookstagram #booklove #comingup #ibizoboi #blackbooks #blacklibrary #freeblackwomenslibrary

#短律句 です
#萩原井泉水
#冬の季語

木の葉が、一枚また一枚落ちる
散るのではなく 落ちる
強い意志が感じられる句ですね

#月曜日おわりました

#会話が噛み合わない #最近よくある光景 😱💦(笑)

#年末調整 #指名願い
#すすまない 
#そだね #metoo #半端ねぇ 
#今年の流行語 😁
#私の流行語は
#なんでやねん #と #おーまいがー
ずーと(笑)
#お疲れ様でした

text:
@yoshitaka_haba #この本買います ^_^
佐久間裕美子さん @yumikosakuma の1年間の日記をまとめた『my little new york times』が発売しました。
この本はn.y.を拠点に政治、社会、文化など幅広い話題を届けてくれる彼女が、「トランプ時代」のアメリカの平熱を伝えるジャーナリスティックな（日々の）心憶え。
ハーヴェイ・ワインスタインに端を発した#metoo のムーヴメントや広がる格差や人種差別の問題、食やファションに対する考え方、書物の未来、この時代に芸術や音楽に触れる意味などなど、長短も様々な365日のイシューが読む側を飽きさせません。
誰かに見られることを意識するかしないかで、日記の種類も随分かわってきますが、本書は明らかに前者。彼女の問題意識を伝える前提で、しかもすべての日記に関連記事のqrコードまで付いているから「日記文学」の内省的な部分が苦手な人も安心してください。
もうひとつ愉快なのは、アメリカ、ペルー、タイ、日本など、とにかく移動し続ける佐久間さんのエネルギー。もともと日記文学は日々の移動を描く紀行文と密接な関係を持っていますが（カエサルの『ガリア戦記』や紀貫之『土佐日記』）、人の生き方の新しい地平を探し考え続ける彼女の走力と持久力には驚きます。
新聞風のエディトリアルデザインやユニークな小口の処理など、読み心地にもこだわった力作はnuma booksから。
また、先週土曜日は金沢のleto @leto_kanazawa で行われた出版記念イベントのゲストとして佐久間さんとお話したのですが、会場の雰囲気、お客様、その後の酒席とどれを取っても最高の夜でした。
佐久間さん、坂矢さん、カイエさん、高木さん、ありがとうございました！
#佐久間裕美子 #mylittlenewyorktimes #numabooks #テロリストの息子 #ヒップな生活革命 #ピンヒールははかない #letokanazawa

text:
nos últimos dias, um novo movimento online vem ganhando força. #whyididntreport é uma campanha criada por internautas para denunciar justamente os porquês de não terem denunciados os assédios sofridos. a atriz lili reinhart aderiu à hashtag e contou sua história: “porque eu não queria perder o meu emprego ou fazer as pessoas pensarem que eu era a rainha do drama”, escreveu no twitter. lili não está sozinha. várias atrizes já disseram que se calaram ou foram caladas após sofrerem assédios em seus respectivos ambientes de trabalho para não terem suas carreiras prejudicadas. e isso não acontece só em hollywood ou com famosas! uma internauta usou a hashtag para dizer que não denunciou o assédio sexual sofrido porque o cara ocupava um cargo importante na empresa em que trabalhava e a intimidou.

outra mulher relatou que foi abusada por um menino da escola católica e levou 45 anos para, finalmente, conseguir falar sobre o assédio. “eu me senti envergonhada e com medo do que os meus colegas de classe pudessem achar de mim”, escreveu. brasileiras também começaram a aderir ao movimento online, inspirado em campanhas como #metoo, #meuprimeiroassédio e #meuqueridoprofessor. a maioria dos depoimentos deixa claro que vergonha, medo e culpa são os principais sentimentos que levam as mulheres a não denunciarem. além disso, muitas não são levadas a sério, inclusive pela justiça, que fazem pouco caso do crime ou dão a entender que ela está louca ou que é apenas um “desentendimento de marido e mulher”. é importante ressaltar que, se você desconfia que algo aconteceu, é porque realmente algo aconteceu. por mais que algumas pessoas tentem te fazer acreditar que não, você tem a palavra final. o brasil é um dos países que mais mata mulheres por crimes de gênero e/ou passionais. no país, o feminicídio mata uma mulher a cada duas horas, de acordo com o mapa da violência do conselho nacional de justiça divulgado em 2016.

e aí, why you didn’t report?

text:
nebula... @paradiseseeds 
quand nous avons développé la #nebula, ce fut un succès pour les cultivateurs d'intérieur qui ont vite repérer le fort potentiel de cette plante à croissance rapide. 
rapidement, elle est devenue un premier choix pour de nombreux vétérans qui recherchaient une sativa avec de bons rendements et un high "à l'ancienne".. elle a été disponible comme variété depuis le milieu des années 90, appartenant à la collection de graines initiales de paradise. 
la génétique de la nebula révèle la clé de son succès : 
elle est composée d'une lignée fruitée et sucrée issue d'une haze américaine dominante et de l'épicée master widow, une white widow croisée dans sa 13e génération (à l'époque) développé par l'éleveur de semences néerlandais ingemar. 
cette belle lignée génétique principalement sativa représente une synthèse parfaite des deux parents, la nebula tend à avoir cette marque de la famille des white widow, cet aspect blanc combiné avec la douceur fruitée et planante du high du parent sativa. ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
#paradiseseeds #grainesdecollection #finestseedcollection #paradiseseedsfrance #france #paris #marseille #lyon #toulouse #thc #cbd

text:
colette(2018)
imdb:6.8/10
metascore:74/100
rotten tomatoes:87%

کولت نام مستعار رمان‌نویس فرانسوی است.در سال ۱۸۹۳ سیدونی گابریل کولت(کیرا نایتلی) با مردی به نام ویلی(دومینیک وست) که ۱۴ سال از او بزرگتر و ناشر معروفی در پاریس است، آشنا می‌شود و با او ازدواج می‌کند. ویلی تمام نوشته‌های کولت را با نام خود به چاپ می‌رساند
.
داستان فیلم دقیقا از زمان آشنایی کولت با ویلی و ازدواج آنها شروع میشود . ما شاهد  فراز و نشیب زندگی زناشویی وی با شوهری زورگو و متقلب،چگونگی شروع به نوشتن کلت  و همچنین تجربه ی جنسی و عاطفی کلت با جنس موافقش،هستیم
.
طراحی صحنه و لباس ،فضا سازی ، فیلمبرداری و دکوپاژ بسیار عالی و حرفه ای به آنها پرداخته شده و فیلم همه این ها رو مدیون  کارگردانی خیلی خوب  واش وستمورلند میباشد. کیرا نایتلی بسیار خوش در این فیلم میدرخشد و یقینا از کاندیدا های بهترین بازیگری نقش اول جایزه اسکار خواهد بود .فیلم خیلی روان و معقول داستانش رو جلو میبره و شما رو سرگرم خودش میکنه
.
بنظرم کارگردان به عمد سراغ نویسندگی و ارزش های رمان نویسی کلت نرفته و نکته ی حائز اهمییت فیلم هم همین است که کارگردان تمام سعی اش را داشته تا توجه بیننده رو به بحث مربوط به زن و جایگاه حقوق زن در جامعه مطرح کند. در واقع جنبشی که از سال ۲۰۰۶ شروع شده و در سال ۲۰۱۷ با رسوایی تهیه کننده معروف هالیوودی هاروی واینستاین توسط اشلی جاد به شدت جان گرفت و با #metoo سرتاسر فضاهای مجازی رو در بر گرفت تا از زنان در برابر ناعدالتی جنسیتی ،تبعیض، اذیت و آزار جنسی ،ضعیف تلقی شدن و در نهایت زورگویی های جنس مذکر به هر نحوی ،حمایت شود . و از موفقییت های بارز این جنبش  که امسال شاهدش هستیم، حضور بسیار موفق و چشمگیر بانوان آمریکایی در صنعت سینما و سریال های هالیوودی چه از لحاظ تجاری و چه از لحاظ هنری ،میباشد
.
دیدن این فیلم خوش ساخت رو به شما عزیزان پیشنهاد میکنم

کولت نام مستعار رمان‌نویس فرانسوی است.در سال ۱۸۹۳ سیدونی گابریل کولت(کیرا نایتلی) با مردی به نام ویلی(دومینیک وست) که ۱۴ سال از او بزرگتر و ناشر معروفی در پاریس است، آشنا می‌شود و با او ازدواج می‌کند. ویلی تمام نوشته‌های کولت را با نام خود به چاپ می‌رساند
.
داستان فیلم دقیقا از زمان آشنایی کولت با ویلی و ازدواج آنها شروع میشود . ما شاهد  فراز و نشیب زندگی زناشویی وی با شوهری زورگو و متقلب،چگونگی شروع به نوشتن کلت  و همچنین تجربه ی جنسی و عاطفی کلت با جنس موافقش،هستیم
.
طراحی صحنه و لباس ،فضا سازی ، فیلمبرداری و دکوپاژ بسیار عالی و حرفه ای به آنها پرداخته شده و فیلم همه این ها رو مدیون  کارگردانی خیلی خوب  واش وستمورلند میباشد. کیرا نایتلی بسیار خوش در این فیلم میدرخشد و یقینا از کاندیدا های بهترین بازیگری نقش اول جایزه اسکار خواهد بود .فیلم خیلی روان و معقول داستانش رو جلو میبره و شما رو سرگرم خودش میکنه
.
بنظرم کارگردان به عمد سراغ نویسندگی و ارزش های رمان نویسی کلت نرفته و نکته ی حائز اهمییت فیلم هم همین است که کارگردان تمام سعی اش را داشته تا توجه بیننده رو به بحث مربوط به زن و جایگاه حقوق زن در جامعه مطرح کند. در واقع جنبشی که از سال ۲۰۰۶ شروع شده و در سال ۲۰۱۷ با رسوایی تهیه کننده معروف هالیوودی هاروی واینستاین توسط اشلی جاد به شدت جان گرفت و با  سرتاسر فضاهای مجازی رو در بر گرفت تا از زنان در برابر ناعدالتی جنسیتی ،تبعیض، اذیت و آزار جنسی ،ضعیف تلقی شدن و در نهایت زورگویی های جنس مذکر به هر نحوی ،حمایت شود . و از موفقییت های بارز این جنبش  که امسال شاهدش هستیم، حضور بسیار موفق و چشمگیر بانوان آمریکایی در صنعت سینما و سریال های هالیوودی چه از لحاظ تجاری و چه از لحاظ هنری ،میباشد
.

text:
в час, когда меня не станет в мыслях ласковых твоих,
я вздрогну в разбитом теле, ополаскивая рыхлое нутро.
какой-то дрянью, фаршированный собой
по мостовой вожу ногами до смешного вразнобой!

из неба сыпется перхоть, перхоть крошками с плеч.
я очернел своей юность самой пошлой из мечт.
да в чёрных тачках, похожих на больших черепах
перекрикивать мысли в чужих черепах.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
you tell a boy that to be a man is to not show any emotions but you excuse anger. you discourage a boy from seeking help and tell him that to be a man is to be able to have it all together at all times and then we wonder why a large proportion of men are perpetrators of violence.
_
everywhere we turn, men and boys are perceived as monsters and toxic masculity seems to be a plague we are all so desperate to wipe out when we are the ones who created the monsters. 
_
society mass produce violent boys and men, unconsciously. we ourselves created the culture of power, privilege and entitlement and violence for our boys and men and the earlier we come to terms with that reality, the easier it will be to eradicate violence against women and girls perpetrated by men.
_
we can achieve a peaceful and just world but not without the help of men. let's get men involved in the conversation on violence against women and girls! 
@uksaysnomore @unitednations @unwomen @acalltomen @heforshe @timesupnow @projectconsent

text:
“i write to listen. i write out of silence. i write to soothe the voices shouting inside me, outside me, all around me. i write because i believe in words. i write because it is a dance with paradox. i write knowing i can be killed by own words, stabbed by syntax, crucified by understanding and misunderstanding. i write past the embarrassment of exposure. i trust nothing especially myself and slide head first into the familiar abyss of doubt and humiliation and threaten to push the delete button on my way down, or madly erase each line, pick up the paper and rip it into shreds — and then i realize it doesn’t matter, words are always a gamble, words are splinters from cut glass. i write because it is dangerous, a bloody risk, like love, to form the words, to say the words, to touch the source, to be touched, to reveal how vulnerable we are, how transient. i write as though i am whispering in the ear of the one i love.” ~ terry tempest williams ~

text:
when you think of farmers and farming, do you think of science and technology?⠀
⠀
there's a reason why agricultural degrees are called bachelor of agricultural science degrees... because farming is science based and today's farming is reliant on technology.⠀
⠀
i'm very proud to have a bachelor of science degree but i'm even more proud of the way simply rose petals has used science to produce the most cutting edge rose petals and edible flowers in the world.⠀
⠀
our freeze driers are technical and scientific and i used every ounce of my scientific knowledge to develop a technique that produces the highest quality freeze dried flowers in the world.⠀
⠀
my mother is pictured here with one of our smaller freeze driers. every day a whole host of data is recorded for every single freeze drier and then analysed by mum to ensure their smooth operation.⠀
⠀
like every successful farmer today, my mother and i have had to take a scientific and technological approach to farming. ⠀
⠀
mum operates our freeze driers with such precision that she will even notice the slightest change in data well before any problem has been discovered. ⠀
⠀
many people doubted that mum and i had the mechanical or technological expertise to operate such heavy machinery, especially in a rural area with limited support. ⠀
⠀
i'm here to tell you that you can do whatever you put your mind to - male or female. mum and i are living proof that female farmers are capable, scientific and tech savvy.⠀
⠀
we are precise. ⠀
we are detailed. ⠀
we produce world class product. ⠀
we are the 2018 winner of the victorian regional award for agricultural innovation.⠀
⠀
sarah rose bloom xx 🌹😊 📷 @jephchen

text:
frida kahlo was a really amazing woman. the story of her life and her way of expressing herself in art made her a myth, but what i admire most about her is the way in which she created her own character little by little. his folkloric clothes, his stone necklaces, his plants and his pets that surrounded him in his little house full of mud basins. it was all part of that character she portrayed and who had real life in her own life. she was the creator of herself. lying on her bed looking at herself in the mirror suffering pain but surrounded by paintings and colors, she got to be known all over the world and fill every place on the planet with her image and be an icon of fashion nowadays. i needed to think about her and understand her work and the best way to do it was to give her life in my own home, with my own hands, and at least if not forever, to have her with me and receive a little bit of her light. she is in barcelona in a place where every day shines with her presence.
.
painting on canvas 130x195
price € 2.700
.
frida kahlo fue funa mujer realmente increíble. la historia de su vida y su forma de expresarse  a si misma en el arte la convirtieron en un mito, pero lo que más me gusta de ella es la forma en que poco a poco fue creando su propio personaje. su ropa folklórica, sus collares de piedra, sus plantas y sus mascotas que lo rodeaban en su casita llena de vasijas de barro. todo era parte de ese personaje que ella retrató y que tenía vida real en su propia vida. postrada en su cama mirándose al espejo sufriendo de dolor pero rodeada de pinturas y colores, ella consiguió ser conocida por el mundo entero y llenar cada rincón del planeta con su imagen y ser un icono de moda en la actualidad, casi un siglo después. necesitaba pensar en ella y comprender su obra y la mejor manera de hacerlo fué dándole vida en mi propia casa, y al menos aunque no sea para siempre, poder tenerla conmigo y recibir un poquito de su luz.

text:
"маньяки блаженствуют на свете..."
главный сукин сын мирового кинематографа (причем в буквальном, а не пушкинском смысле) ларс фон триер в своем последнем фильме "доме, который построил джек" выглядит заправским маньяком, убивающим женщин и детей. на каннском фестивале, где фильм показывали вне конкурса, публика возмущалась и массово уходила с показа. но в целом непонятно почему. триер и до этого, до движения #metoo, убивал женщин (в "антихристе"), доказывал, что любой дом/цивилизация построены на костях и насилии (в "догвилле"), издевался над религией (в "рассекая волны") и разнес к чертям всю планету (в "меланхолии"). пожалуй, "джек", несмотря на концентрацию в нем убийств, не так уж и радикален концептуально. стоит ли его все-таки смотреть? да в двух случаях. если вы ничего не знаете про фон триера, то в этом фильме получите его в концентрированном виде, в авторском самопересказе и тем самым решите, надо ли знакомится с ним поближе. а если вы любите его, как я за "догвиль", "королевство" и "нимфоманку", то просто еще раз скоротаете с этим ироничным маньяком вечерок. кстати, имя героя вержа (verge), который в фильме, словно вергилий из "божественной комедии", ведет маньяка джека по кругам ада, на французском значит "член". ох предполагаю, такое имя триер выбрал не случайно, а специально для каннского кинофестиваля, с которого 7 лет назад был с позором изгнан за свое неадекватное поведение. типа нате, выкусите.
.
.
#киноман #кино #фильм #фонтриер #хорошеекино #артхаус #джек #фестивальноекино #люблюкино #каннскийфестиваль

'' главный сукин сын мирового кинематографа ( причем в буквальном , а не пушкинском смысле ) ларс фон триер в своем последнем фильме `` доме , который построил джек '' выглядит заправским маньяком , убивающим женщин и детей . на каннском фестивале , где фильм показывали вне конкурса , публика возмущалась и массово уходила с показа . но в целом непонятно почему . триер и до этого , до движения убивал женщин ( в `` антихристе '' ) , доказывал , что любой дом/цивилизация построены на костях и насилии ( в `` догвилле '' ) , издевался над религией ( в `` рассекая волны '' ) и разнес к чертям всю планету ( в `` меланхолии '' ) . пожалуй , `` джек '' , несмотря на концентрацию в нем убийств , не так уж и радикален концептуально . стоит ли его все-таки смотреть ? да в двух случаях . если вы ничего не знаете про фон триера , то в этом фильме получите его в концентрированном виде , в авторском самопересказе и тем самым решите , надо ли знакомится с ним поближе . а если вы любите его , как я за `` догвиль '' , `` королевство '' и `` нимфоманку '' , то просто еще раз скоротаете с этим ироничным маньяком вечерок . кстати , имя героя вержа ( verge ) , который в фильме , словно вергилий из `` божественной комедии '' , ведет маньяка джека по кругам ада , на французском значит `` член '' . ох предполагаю , такое имя триер выбрал не случайно , а специально для каннского кинофестиваля , с которого 7 лет назад был с позором изгнан за свое неадекватное поведение . типа нате , выкусите . . .

text: hoy fue un día glorioso. 🤩 hoy fuimos testigos del poder que tenemos de generar cambios desde nuestros espacios. 🙌@angelaponceofficial con una clara demostración de grandeza y nobleza nos dio una gran lección de #liderazgo e #igualdad al retar estructuras sociales caducas con tan sólo participar en el  #missuniverse #2018 🌏. esto no se trataba de ganar una corona, se trataba de poner los verdaderos temas de fondo en nuestras mesas durante un domingo cualquiera. 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦#feminismo , #migracion , #educación , #pobreza , #empleoinformal , #marihuanalegal , #empoderamiento #femenino , #estereotipos de #genero e #igualdad  entraron en la casa de millones de ciudadanos del mundo a través de un punto en común: #belleza, esa belleza que tiene como base nuestra #humanidad , acompañada de empatía, solidaridad y el propósito de dejar un mundo mejor. ¡ #angelaponce qué grande, qué valiente, qué gran mujer! 💃🏽 no podríamos estar más orgullosas de celebrar nuestra #feminidad y continuar por la lucha por nuestros #derechoshumanos en un momento histórico tan poderoso e inspirador, precisamente por #mujeres como tú. gracias por tanto ⭐️ la corona más importante te la llevas tú y es la del honor de luchar causas justas en nombre propio y de tant@s otr@s. 👑 en el primer episodio de nuestro podcast #subversiva hablábamos justamente de la necesidad de hacer historia (link in bio) 💪🏻 estamos juntas en esto #sororidad 💁🏽‍♀️ es nuestro turno #timesup #metoo #yotambien #trans #transexual #transgender #queer #lgbt

text:
“la transformación depende de todes” laura azcurra, de @actrices.argentinas, explica cómo se organizó la denuncia contra darthes. por sonia santoro / @pagina12, 17 de diciembre de 2018.
.
"desde que thelma fardin llegó al colectivo, hubo un trabajo pensado para apoyar a la actriz en su denuncia judicial y hacerlo públicamente con alto impacto. cómo se gestó la movida, las repercusiones, la gente que la para en la calle para agradecer y contar sus abusos"(...) .
“la transformación depende de todes. no solamente de nosotras las actrices que tenemos visibilidad”. dice laura azcurra, la actriz que tuvo la responsabilidad de conducir la conferencia de prensa en la que thelma fardin denunció a juan darthes rodeada del colectivo de actrices argentinas; un grupo reunido al calor de la lucha por conseguir el aborto legal, seguro y gratuito, que sigue abrazando la amplitud de causas que engloba el feminismo. .
en esta entrevista, azcurra repasa el antes y el después de la denuncia y propone que toda la sociedad se haga cargo del cambio: “ya no se puede patear la pelota. ni a los diputados, ni solo a los jueces... sino que individualmente y personalmente, desde cada rincón como ciudadano, humano e inquilino del mundo, es una decisión y una responsabilidad propia” (...) .
nota completa: https://www.pagina12.com.ar/162647-la-transformacion-depende-de-todes

text:
5 คำถามสุดโหด ที่สะท้อนถึงความสนใจที่มีในโลกได้เป็นอย่างดี
.
1. เสรีภาพสื่อสำคัญอย่างไร?
มิสเปอร์โตริโก้: หน้าที่ของสื่อคือการนำเสนอข่าวสาร ว่าอะไรเป็นเรื่องสำคัญ ณ เวลานั้นๆ พวกเขาควรมีเสรีภาพในการนำเสนอว่ามีเหตุการณ์อะไรเกิดขึ้นบ้าง แต่พวกเขาก็ต้องไม่ลืมความเห็นอกเห็นใจผู้อื่น เพราะในโลกตอนนี้ก็มีปัญหาที่แตกต่างกัน
.
2. การเคลื่อนไหว #metoo ทำให้โลกกังวลความถูกต้องทางการเมืองมากไปหรือเปล่า?
มิสเวียดนาม: ฉันไม่คิดว่ามันมากเกินไปนะคะ การปกป้องสตรี และสิทธิสตรีเป็นเรื่องที่ถูกต้องเหมาะสม ผู้หญิงต้องการการปกป้องและสิทธิที่เหมาะสม
.
3. กัญชาถูกกฎหมาย เห็นด้วยหรือไม่?
มิสฟิลิปปินส์: ฉันสนับสนุนกัญชาทางการแพทย์ แต่ไม่ใช่เพื่อความสนุกค่ะ ถ้ามีคนโต้แย้งว่า อ้าวบุหรี่และเครื่องดื่มแอลกอฮอล์หละ ฉันก็จะบอกว่าทุกอย่างดีหมดแหละ แต่มันต้องมีความพอดีนะคะ
.
4. แต่ละประเทศควรจำกัดผู้ลี้ภัยหรือไม่?
มิสแอฟริกาใต้: ฉันคิดว่าแต่ละประเทศควรมีกฎระเบียบของตนเอง แต่ในสังคมที่เติบโต เราต้องเข้าใจว่าพวกเราคล้ายกันอย่างหนึ่งคือเราล้วนเป็นมนุษย์ เราควรเปิดใจรับและรักผู้อื่นไม่ว่าเราจะมาจากไหนก็ตาม
.
5. การประกวดนางงามขัดกับสิทธิสตรีนิยมหรือไม่?
มิสเวเนซูเอล่า: เราอยู่ในยุคที่มีพัฒนาการมาไกลมาก การประกวดนางงามมันไม่ใช่แค่เรื่องความสวย แต่ยังเป็นเรื่องของหัวใจ ความรู้สึก ความอ่อนโยน การประกวดนางงามเป็นตัวตอกย้ำว่าผู้หญิงอย่างฉันสามารถประสบความสำเร็จระดับโลกได้
.

มิสแอฟริกาใต้: ฉันคิดว่าแต่ละประเทศควรมีกฎระเบียบของตนเอง แต่ในสังคมที่เติบโต เราต้องเข้าใจว่าพวกเราคล้ายกันอย่างหนึ่งคือเราล้วนเป็นมนุษย์ เราควรเปิดใจรับและรักผู้อื่นไม่ว่าเราจะมาจากไหนก็ตาม
.
5. การประกวดนางงามขัดกับสิทธิสตรีนิยมหรือไม่?
มิสเวเนซูเอล่า: เราอยู่ในยุคที่มีพัฒนาการมาไกลมาก การประกวดนางงามมันไม่ใช่แค่เรื่องความสวย แต่ยังเป็นเรื่องของหัวใจ ความรู้สึก ความอ่อนโยน การประกวดนางงามเป็นตัวตอกย้ำว่าผู้หญิงอย่างฉันสามารถประสบความสำเร็จระดับโลกได้
.

stem_filter: 5 คำถามสุดโหด ที่สะท้อนถึงความสนใจที่มีในโลกได้เป็นอย่างดี . 1 . เสรีภาพสื่อสำคัญอย่างไร ? มิสเปอร์โตริโก้ : หน้าที่ของสื่อคือการนำเสนอข่าวสาร ว่าอะไรเป็นเรื่องสำคัญ ณ เวลานั้นๆ พวกเขาควรมีเสรีภาพในการนำเสนอว่ามีเหตุการณ์อะไรเกิดขึ้นบ้าง แต่พวกเขาก็ต้องไม่ลืมความเห็นอกเห็นใจผู้อื่น เพราะในโลกตอนนี้ก็มีปัญหาที่แตกต่างกัน . 2 . การเคลื่อนไหว ทำให้โลกกังวลความถูกต้องทางการเมืองมากไปหรือเปล่า ? มิสเวียดนาม : ฉันไม่คิดว่ามันมากเกินไปนะคะ การปกป้องสตรี และสิทธิสตรีเป็นเรื่องที่ถูกต้องเหมาะสม ผู้หญิงต้องการการปกป้องและสิทธิที่เหมาะสม . 3 . กัญชาถูกกฎหมาย เห็นด้วยหรือไม่ ? มิสฟิลิปปินส์ : ฉันสนับสนุนกัญชาทางการแพทย์ แต่ไม่ใช่เพื่อความสนุกค่ะ ถ้ามีคนโต้แย้งว่า อ้าวบุหรี่และเครื่องดื่มแอลกอฮอล์หละ ฉันก็จะบอกว่าทุกอย่างดีหมดแหละ แต่มันต้องมีความพอดีนะคะ . 4 . แต่ละประเทศควรจำกัดผู้ลี้ภัยหรือไม่ ? มิสแอฟริกาใต้ : ฉันคิดว่าแต่ละประเทศควรมีกฎระเบียบของตนเอง แต่ในสังคมที่เติบโต เราต้องเข้าใจว่าพวกเราคล้ายกันอย่างหนึ่งคือเราล้วนเป็นมนุษย์ เราควรเปิดใจรับและรักผู้อื่นไม่ว่าเราจะมาจากไหนก็ตาม . 5 . การประกวดนางงามขัดกับสิทธิสตรีนิยมหรือไม่ ? มิสเวเนซูเอล่า : เราอยู่ในยุคที่มีพัฒนาการมาไกลมาก การประกวดนางงามมันไม่ใช่แค่เรื่องความสวย แต่ยังเป็นเรื่องของหัวใจ ความรู้สึก ความอ่อนโยน การประกวดนางงามเป็นตัวตอกย้ำว่าผู้หญิงอย่างฉันสามารถประสบความสำเร็จระดับโลกได้ .

text:
no te confundas.
no es "feminismo", la otra cara de la misma moneda...
no es querer generar mas separación y distancia entre géneros...
no es violencia encubierta, ahora hacia los hombres,
ni creernos "mas o mejores" que ellos, 
ni cerrarles la puerta...
no es falta de amor, integración o confianza,
no es querer negarlos o hacer juicios que condenan.

no nos estamos revelando a su fuerza, 
a su masculinidad, a su esencia...
no te confundas.

es el grito ancestral que nos habita
que hoy  pega su alarido.
son cientos y miles de años de violencia incrustada,
de callarnos, de bajar la mirada y apretar los dientes.

es la información de miles de años, 
grabada en nuestras células,
la que esta aullando como una loca.
son todas nuestras abuelas ancestras caminándonos la piel.
humilladas, negadas, abusadas, avergonzadas, quemadas, golpeadas, torturadas, violadas, mutiladas, encerradas, 
calladas, sometidas al silencio del poder masculino, 
por siglos.

no te confundas. 
no soy yo, mujer, ni ella, mujer... es el alarido de todas ellas juntas que nos habitan y nos mueven.
y dicen basta. 
nos hemos despertado 
del tiempo de la sumisión y el silencio,
de las lagrimas y el golpe
de presuponer invisibles nuestras emociones.

sentimos. 
y estamos vivas.

no te confundas.
no es un movimiento feminista el que esta tomando voz y forma,
son nuestras miles de abuelas que están vivas
caminando las calles, hablando en los medios,
buscando sanar, ser escuchadas, perdonar, 
desanclar tantos siglos de dolor enterrado en el cuerpo,
y en el alma...
gritan desde nuestro propio holograma interno
polinizan nuestros discursos y miradas.

por fin, hablan.

somos todas todo. 
pasado presente y futuro.
somos la voz de las sinvoz. 
y nuestro andar recupera todos los pasos enterrados. ( eva )

text:
where all my pistanthrophobes at 🙋🏻‍♀️
.
.
it’s totally normal and acceptable to have this fear when one has experienced such trauma (especially this twisted type of abuse). but don’t let this hinder you forever. not everyone is bad. not everyone is out to “get you”. i truly believe it starts with personal boundaries and listening to your gut when these giant red flags 🚩 are slapping you across the face. it’s about recognizing the signs of love bombing vs courting. .
.
be a pistanthrophobe today but just be a wiser, stronger version of that tomorrow and every day until you’re ready to let love in again 💜

text: i think we lie to ourselves that we believe who we are due to the social expectations placed around us. we contort ourselves to what people wish to believe we are, we attempt to control our persona, we live the lie people wish of us....yet we struggle. the pain of what we are surrounds us. each day it is inescapable. two halves must make a whole. our true selves can be left, right, and halves of each. both do make a whole...in time. if we don’t except ourselves for who we are (and we should) or what we have faced, we can never live for ourselves. if we don’t love ourselves we can never truly love another. regardless of the path that may or may not lay ahead, i don’t wish to be anything but myself. i won’t let my life be what others want anymore. i can not. i will not. no more. rape should end and no spouse is property. #nomore #metoo #metoomovement #livingagain #living #lifequotes #lifelivedbeautifully #beautifulwomen #lgbtqia #endrapeculture

text:
what are jesus’ issues and concerns?

i think that jesus would be mainly concerned and would dislike, not people, but actions of violence, hate, and discrimination, especially towards children. for example, police brutality is something that crosses racial discrimination and violence, which are two things that jesus wouldn’t like, as his love for his brothers and sisters is strong. also, immigration laws, as they prevent other humans, who we should love instead of hate, from living a life of peace in a better place. jesus would focus on advocating for people who are being mistreated or taken advantage of, such as victims of the #metoo movement, as well as gender inequality, racial inequality, people subject to sex trafficking, etc. he also, shown in multiple scripture passages, has a soft spot for children, and would probably be sad that, nowadays, fewer and fewer children being pulled into knowledge of him and god, so maybe he would be like a large scale missionary? he would want to give all children, but especially mistreated children, equity, happiness, education, opportunities, and more.

matthew 19:14 
jesus said, “let the little children come to me, and do not hinder them, for the kingdom of heaven belongs to such as these.”

text:
age 13 in this photograph in iowa. throughout the state, small town meets city life in unique and inviting ways. a #community, in particular, that has the best of both worlds. a little bit out of town, and you’ll be met with #beautiful rolling fields, quaint shops, and historical treasures in friendly little towns.

a nice place, a place where i first watched #janetjacksons video #if. today, still one of my fave music videos. a trip-hop fever dream of distorted guitars, trance-like backing vocals, including janet’s erotic mumbles. an #impressive feat to make a song that #sounds as if it’s from the #future. 
janet as she emerges from a windblown poof of red curtains in the video, an epic entrance indeed. the video as a whole was full on #japanica during that time — a rich depiction of a #tokyo-style video bar, which was great for me as a fan of #manga too. the video’s famous voguing-meets-capoeira breakdown, this song, and #video remains for me not just her pinnacle but also the pinnacle of her longtime collaborators #jimmyjam and #terrylewis. 
#janetjackson has earned a place in the #rocknroll hall of fame alongside her brothers in the #jackson5, 21 years after their induction. it has taken this long due to #lesmoonves 
hopefully the video i produce next year, will be just as memorable as #if

text: dear sahm...hi there, i’m a working mom. and, from what i can see, we are more alike than different. but when i see facebook and instagram posts, it feels like it’s all turning into a competition of who is working harder or who has a tougher time...but why? i think motherhood is a team sport, and we need each other. we need to understand each other, and see things in different perspectives. so with that, i want you to know a few things from my perspective. first, i do not believe that you do nothing all day, you work your ass off to take care of your child/children every day - most of the time you do this alone. not only that but you probably are trying to get a million other things done too. i admire you for your patience and for handling every single thing! next, work is not a break for us working moms. we have deadlines, bosses, coworkers, clients, and most of the time no lunch break...when we get that dreaded call, “your daughter/son is sick they need to be picked up...” we have to drop everything we are doing and rush home. this call is a constant fear especially when in the middle of stressful situations at work. also, i don’t know if you know this, but i don’t just want your friendship...i need it! i see so many posts on facebook and instagram about moms group events, and meet ups with other moms and babies and i in a way feel envious of the friendships building around me as i can’t make any of those during the week. that tribe everyone has, it’s harder to find and build as a working mom. don’t think i don’t want to be there, because more often then not i wish i could just skip work and be there just like everyone else. lastly, don’t listen to the posts out there..i did not choose my career over spending time with my child. unfortunately, this hurts the most, nobody accuses significant others of this.. i work because i love what i do, and i am able to contribute to our finances. but i am also part of the women in the work place who push for equal pay for women, maternity benefits, etc. i want my daughter to have it better when/if she decides to begin a career in the future - this goes for your daughter too. so sahm you see, let’s do this together. ❤️

text:
trigger warning: sexual assault

last week i ran into a rapist at target.

he isn't my story. he's someone else's but he's a rapist all the same.

i went to get coffee and my phone took a shit. i strolled to the back of the store to see if maybe the tech dept could help.

he was stocking some shit. he looked up and smiled at me, face full of recognition.

i didn't recognize him and i felt my face do that thing it does when i seriously fucking confused. i kept walking.

it wasn't until i caught how short his name was on his nametag and the letter a that my brain lit up. bright red letters: rapist.

i told my bf and he checked to try and ease my worry. we looked him up on fb and sure enough there he was.

he lives in our city. he works at target.

it took 3 days for me to realize the gravity of the trigger.

bc although he isn't my story. he is living the same consequence free life that my abuser is living.

his victims didn't feel comfortable reporting and i understand that. bc i did and it didn't fucking matter.

he gets to walk around like he didn't hurt anyone. like he didn't steal my childhood from me. like he doesn't still darken the corners of my dreams sometimes.

i will rise. and i will take back the small amount of discomfort seeing him shook loose. bc he doesn't deserve that power. i acknowledge the validity of the feeling and i release that shit.

you are not alone. we are not alone. i believe survivors and i hold space for you in whatever part of your journey you're in right now.

tweet_full:
trigger warning: sexual assault

last week i ran into a rapist at target.

he is not my story. he's someone else's but he's a rapist all the same.

i went to get coffee and my phone took a shit. i strolled to the back of the store to see if maybe the tech dept could help.

he was stocking some shit. he looked up and smiled at me, face full of recognition.

i didn't recognize him and i felt my face do that thing it does when i seriously fucking confused. i kept walking.

it wasn't until i caught how short his name was on his nametag and the letter a that my brain lit up. bright red letters: rapist.

i told my bf and he checked to try and ease my worry. we looked him up on fb and sure enough there he was.

he lives in our city. he works at target.

it took 3 days for me to realize the gravity of the trigger.

bc although he is not my story. he is living the same consequence free life that my abuser is living.

his victims didn't feel comfortable reporting and i understand that. bc i did and it didn't fucking matter.

he gets to walk around like he didn't hurt anyone. like he didn't steal my childhood from me. like he does not still darken the corners of my dreams sometimes.

i will rise. and i will take back the small amount of discomfort seeing him shook loose. bc he does not deserve that power. i acknowledge the validity of the feeling and i release that shit.

you are not alone. we are not alone. i believe survivors and i hold space for you in whatever part of your journey you are in right now.

#metoo
.
.
.

text: “this past year we have been experiencing a strong backlash from the cis- male students in the @safeteen programs in schools. they claim they are afraid of being falsely accused of sexual assault. we know that only 2-7% of reported assaults are false and that no one lies about rape any more than about any other crime...(fbi) and yet the idea that females will accuse males out of revenge or malice persists. given how incredibly hard it is to get a conviction and the horror show women have to go through in the process, it boggles the mind that people think women would do this on a whim. the #metoo movement has helped women find their voices and speak the truth about what is, and has been for millennia, an epidemic of violence against women. if males are concerned they need to be vigilant about getting enthusiastic consent. as they should be, as they always should have been. when guys say they are getting mixed messages perhaps they could be encouraged to read this as a “no”. or at least as a moment to ask what’s going on. it’s always bothered me when men say they didn’t know..or couldn’t tell that a woman wasn’t fully on board. after all, even a dog can tell when someone is anxious. when a person is raped, they are in a kind of prison and for many it’s a life sentence. yes, it is truly horrific for someone to be falsely accused,  but it is it more horrific than being raped and have no one believe you?  dear good men: if you don’t harm women then relax, this isn’t about you.” shared by @safeteen vancouver.  #metoo #webelieveher #consent #consentissexy #enthusiasticconsent

text:
दिसंबर 2018 को ngo जीवन अर्थ फाउंडेशन ने जयपुर के अलियावास गाँव चाकसू तहसील में एक महिला स्वास्थ जागरूकता शिविर लगाया जिसमे गाँव के कई लोगो ने बढ़ चढ़ कर हिस्सा लिया। इस शिविर का मुख्य कारण था कि गाँव में महिलाएँ अपनी सेहत को लेकर लापरवाह थी। छोटी छोटी चीज़ें जैसे कि माहवारी के दिनों में पुराने कपड़ो का इस्तेमाल या सूट वगैरह के कत्तर का इस्तेमाल, राख का इस्तेमाल या फिर कागज़ का इस्तेमाल। इस सब के चलते इन औरतों को कईं समस्याओं का सामना करना पड़ रहा था, अपनी जीवनशैली में। शिविर में यह पाया गया कि महिलाएं इन समस्याओं से इतना प्रभावित थी कि उन्हें यह समस्याएं मामूली या स्वाभाविक लगने लगी थी। इन सभी का समाधान करने पहुँची संस्था जीवन अर्थ फाउंडेशन कि टीम एवं उनके साथ समस्त डॉक्टर्स, डॉक्टर पंखुरी जो कि गाइनेकोलॉजिस्ट हैं और डॉक्टर एल एन मीणा जो कि सांस संबंधित समस्याओं का निवारण करते हैं। शिविर में हीमोग्लोबिन, बीपी, ब्लड शुगर, अस्थमा जैसी कईं बीमारियों का नि:शुल्क जाँच किया गया। इस शिविर को मुख्य तौर से मदद प्रदान करने के लिए docconsult आगे आया जिनकी सहायता के बिना यह शिविर सम्भव नहीं हो पाता। इसी दौरान संस्था जीवन अर्थ फाउंडेशन ने शिविर में आयी सभी महिलाओं को सैनिटरी नैपकिन्स बांटे एवं उनसे निवेदन भी किया कि वह इन्ही का इस्तेमाल भी करें। शिविर में ना ही सिर्फ बिमारियों का निवारण किया, बल्कि लोगो को बीमारियों से बचने एवं लड़ने के लिए जागरूक भी किया। ____________

translation: on 9th december 2018, ngo jeevan arth foundation organized a woman's health camp in chaksu village, jaipur. the camp aimed at spreading awareness regarding women's health in which hundreds of women took part along with men and children.

the main cause of organizing the camp was that the women in the village were not keeping good care of their health. considering menstrual health which was found to be the worst as per the survey, we managed to provide medicines, health check up status sheet and other facilities to these women.

in the camp, when we talked to the women, we found that the women were facing terrible health problems not for some days, but for months and years. the shocking revelation was when we found that these women accepted their deteriorated health to be "okay".
name: Jeevan Arth Foundation (NGO)

.
.

deep, slow breaths stimulate the relaxation response in your body
.
also known as the #parasympathetic nervous system (pns)
.
the best way to breathe slowly is to be aware of your breathing by counting your breaths
.
if/when other thoughts come up you will loose count...thus, counting is good training for focusing the mind .

text:
19 months and 16 days later, i have finally rid myself of this reminder. .
the last person to sit on this chair was someone who i thought was my friend. someone who i trusted enough to allow to come into my apartment. someone i’ve known for twenty years. someone who i no longer speak to, and i am perfectly okay with that. the last person to sit in this chair was a rapist. mine. .
i’m not sure why, but the whole situation has been weighing on me for the last two months. every time the dogs ripped more stuffing out of the cushion. every time i moved the chair so i could workout. every time i put it back so i could have what appeared to be a livable space. it’s too bad because i was really proud of having real living room furniture again... and for paying for it in cash because, well, dave ramsey. and i was really mad because i owned this furniture for all of two months before i hated it. .
i thought i needed help to move it, but you know that feeling you get when you have a goal and you would do anything to reach it? that was me with this. i had to dig deep, but i picked this stupid chair up and carried it out the door and up the stairs and halfway to the dumpster. (thanks, joel and autumn, for helping me find the physical strength and chris for helping me find the mental strength.) when i couldn’t carry it anymore, i cried in the middle of the parking lot for a minute and just decided to roll it through the snow. (fresh snow, by the way. another like 3-4” just fell tonight!) .
today, the chair is gone. there is still one more weight from that night that i can’t get rid of yet. the time will come for that. .
tonight, sitting in my living room, i feel so much lighter. i am one step closer to living my best life despite the obstacles. i promised myself to unhook the ball and chain that has been holding me back, and i think this is a good push forward.
name: Carrie Dawley
tweet_full:
19 months and 16 days later, i have finally rid myself of this reminder. .
the last person to sit on this chair was someone who i thought was my friend. someone who i trusted enough to allow to come into my apartment. someone i’ve known for twenty years. someone who i no longer speak to, and i am perfectly okay with that. the last person to sit in this chair was a rapist. mine. .
i’m not sure why, but the whole situation has been weighing on me for the last two months. every time the dogs ripped more stuffing out of the cushion. every time i moved the chair so i could workout. every time i put it back so i could have what appeared to be a livable space. it’s too bad because i was really proud of having real living room furniture again... and for paying for it in cash because, well, dave ramsey. and i was really mad because i owned this furniture for all of two months before i hated it. .
i thought i needed help to move it, but you know that feeling you get when you have a goal and you would do anything to reach it? that was me with this. i had to dig deep, but i picked this stupid chair up and carried it out the door and up the stairs and halfway to the dumpster. (thanks, joel and autumn, for helping me find the physical strength and chris for helping me find the mental strength.) when i couldn’t carry it anymore, i cried in the middle of the parking lot for a minute and just decided to roll it through the snow. text:
this piece of shit's name is jacob walter anderson. he was indicted on 4 counts of sexual assault, yet won't spend a single day in prison. a plea agreement allowed the former baylor university student to plead no contest to a lesser charge of unlawful restraint. 
if the 24-year-old successfully completes three years of deferred probation and pays a $400 fine, his criminal record will be wiped clean of the charge, and he won't have to register as a sex offender. [what in the actual fuck is going on here????]
"the evidence is incredible. he nearly choked her to death. he raped her violently. he left her passed out in her own vomit -- the rape exam confirmed rape," stated vic feazell, the woman's attorney. 
she (the victim) lambasted the court for accepting the plea agreement.
"i am devastated by your decision to let my rapist jacob walter anderson go free without any punishment," the woman said. "he is now free to roam society, stalk women and no one will know he is a sex offender. jacob anderson and all rapists who get away with their crimes will never be cured, never change. if anything they will be emboldened by their power over women and their ability to escape justice and punishment."
i am choosing not to post any of the specific, extremely troubling allegations in any more detail, as they caused me, an assault survivor, to rage like a mother fucker. 
this piece of shit's name is jacob walter anderson. reminds me of another piece of shit named brock turner. #thetimeforjusticeisnow #stophelpingrapistsbeatthesystem #metoo

text:
“predadores sexuais, abuso de poder e silêncio” “o predador pode estar em qualquer um de nossos contextos e usa, acima de tudo, sua posição de poder para subjugar a vítima, buscando a cumplicidade de uma sociedade acostumada a olhar para o outro lado.

poderíamos dizer, quase sem medo de errar, que estamos vivendo um momento muito interessante do ponto de vista social e psicológico. um momento, para muitos, esperado e até mesmo necessário. depois que o caso do produtor de filmes harvey weinstein foi descoberto, a onda expansiva e da mídia parece não parar. todos os dias nos levantamos com outro nome de um famoso, um ídolo que cai, uma terrível história de abusos sexuais.” agora o médium joão de deus é suspeito de abusos sexuais durante tratamentos espirituais. mais de 300 mulheres afirmam ter sido vítimas do religioso, inclusive sua filha veio a público para fazer denúncias que sofria com os abusos desde os 10 anos de idade.

muitas vezes ouvimos testemunhos de atos que aconteceram há mais de 10, 15 ou 20 anos. o véu parece ter caído independentemente do tempo passado, porque a ferida, é claro, permanece latente. é agora que uma realidade que sempre foi conhecida, mas estruturalmente silenciada e implicitamente consentida, começa a vir à tona.” é hora de mudar e quando alguém te pedir ajudar, um pedido de socorro parar de dizer... “isso é perigoso”, “esqueça”, “vire a página”, “vamos olhar para o outro lado.” “talvez este seja o melhor momento para lhes dar nome, para lhes colocar um rosto e parar de olhar para o outro lado. temos vivido durante muito tempo com medo diante dos que têm o poder, são milhares de vítimas obrigadas a se calar e esquecer. evitemos isso, sejamos sensíveis, sejamos lógicos e paremos os predadores sexuais a tempo.” -

geane pastorello

text:
sometimes all you can do is just pause life and be with yourself. just exist. remind yourself of what that feels like, and of what you want from your life and from yourself. find your purpose. from your dreams and chase them. everything that happens in between you and your purpose or your dreams will either attempt to hold you back and serve as obstacles, or will push you forward and serve as forms of encouragement. it’s all about your mindset. your reactions are all about your perceptions and interpretations. these concepts are everything.

text: if your potential 502 boss ever tells you how hot you are, how you'd make a cute couple, or any remarks about your looks in yoga pants, trust me, no job is worth it! i first voiced concerns when the potential employer said they'd hired a female lawyer for the same reason everyone else did, "because she was cute." i said, "you can't say that," which  was met with laughter. when his direction eventually turned to me personally, i immediately spoke up, "do you sexually harass all your female employees, or just me?" that did not go over well and i was "educated" that i was not being sexually harassed, because they "take that kind of thing really seriously." one the perks of owning your own business as a woman: no male boss to kowtow to...most are good. some, not so much. and some deny your complaints of sexual harassment: no woman one wants to believe this is happening to them, it's scary and confusing...your boss or someone thinking about hiring you, most of all, definitely doesn't want you to think they've done anything inappropriate. be strong, you are not alone in the ranks of women who've been mis-treated by potential employers and then told you are the one who needs to lighten up! #metoo #justrunningmymouth

sylvia plath’s shocking, realistic, and intensely emotional novel about a woman falling into the grip of insanity. 
esther greenwood is brilliant, beautiful, enormously talented, and successful, but slowly going under—maybe for the last time. in her acclaimed and enduring masterwork, sylvia plath brilliantly draws the reader into esther’s breakdown with such intensity that her insanity becomes palpably real, even rational—as accessible an experience as going to the movies. a deep penetration into the darkest and most harrowing corners of the human psyche, the bell jar is an extraordinary accomplishment and a haunting american classic.

#honesty ha that is something that we don’t do often enough. why, well we were all taught at a young age, those “innocent lies-white lies” you know the ones, when the phones rang, and the kids answered “tell them mommy is busy or in the shower” we teach them about santa, easter bunny, and all those things that we’ve made an addition, a “i gotta have it or extreme  i just want it!” there are so many examples i could be here all day. being honest has finally made me #spiritual in a way that i could never have imagined! you don’t have to be harsh, there is a #kindness in the way you speak that can heal others! #seekpeace #seekthetruth #truth #honesty 
@@@@@@@

#honesty ha that is something that we don’t do often enough. why, well we were all taught at a young age, those “innocent lies-white lies” you know the ones, when the phones rang, and the kids answered “tell them mommy is busy or in the shower” we teach them about santa, easter bunny, and all those things that we’ve made an addition, a “i gotta have it or extreme  i just want it!” there are so many examples i could be here all day. being honest has finally made me #spiritual in a way that i could never have imagined! you don’t have to be harsh, there is a #kindness in the way you speak that can heal others! #seekpeace #seekthetruth #truth #honesty 
@@@@@@@

text: #metoo
name: Ciara Starr Yes its ME
tweet_full: #metoo

text:
💭 estoy harta de escuchar "quizá no sea cierto lo que ella dice o lo malinterpretó". la idea de que las mujeres son exageradas es un prejuicio que invalida las experiencias de las mujeres y eso nos pone en desventaja de entrada; ¿por qué? si fuera cierto el testimonio que desacreditan, serían cómplices, soporte de su realización y reproducción.

los silencios no son políticamente correctos, son cómplices porque la experiencia masculina y femenina está edificada sobre prejuicios que muchos no se han tomado la molestia de poner en cuestión. "no le creo, estas feminazis ven machismo en todo"... quizá sí lo hay y les incomoda más su denuncia que dar el beneficio de la duda respecto a su presencia en diferentes ámbitos y niveles. "si es cierto lo que ella dice, seguro se lo ganó". nadie merece ser violentado, no somos animales como para creer que no podemos discutir y solucionar nuestros problemas, pero es más fácil negarlos. si la vida se basara en lo más fácil, sería muy mediocre y aburrida. pero aquí se trata de arreglar el problema de la violencia de género hacia las mujeres, así que vamos construyendo y hablando a quien tenga el valor de escuchar, ver, cuestionarse, buscar y actuar.

que todas las voces sean escuchadas. #miracomonosponemos (vean el hashtag en twitter y si son mujeres y quieren unirse, compartan esta imagen o pónganla de foto de perfil). #yositecreo #metoo #yotambien #feminismo #mujer #mujeres #mexico #latinoamerica

text:
.
.
ラーレ・イスタンブール (lale istanbul)は、トルコ製のインテリアやファッションアクセサリーを中心にセレクトしたアイテムをご紹介しております。.
.
＊「ラーレ・イスタンブール」について...
.
ラーレ (lale) とは...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)
.
イスタンブール (istanbul) とは...
「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。
.
ラーレ・イスタンブール 公式ブランドサイト
www.laleistanbul.com
.
onlinestore、twitter、facebookのフォローもどうぞ宜しくお願いいたします。

.
.
ラーレ・イスタンブール (lale istanbul)は、トルコ製のインテリアやファッションアクセサリーを中心にセレクトしたアイテムをご紹介しております。.
.
＊「ラーレ・イスタンブール」について...
.
ラーレ (lale) とは...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)
.
イスタンブール (istanbul) とは...
「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。
.
ラーレ・イスタンブール 公式ブランドサイト
www.laleistanbul.com
.
onlinestore、twitter、facebookのフォローもどうぞ宜しくお願いいたします。

.
ラーレ・イスタンブール (lale istanbul)は、トルコ製のインテリアやファッションアクセサリーを中心にセレクトしたアイテムをご紹介しております。.
.
＊「ラーレ・イスタンブール」について...
.
ラーレ (lale) とは...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)
.
イスタンブール (istanbul) とは...
「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。
.

text:
🙌🏼🔊 #loveyourself #liveyourlife #fuckhaters #howitsdone — for the first time in the miss universe’s 66-year history, there is a #transgender contestant in the competition.
-
angela ponce, 27, who is miss spain, is the first transgender beauty queen in the #missuniverse competition. she will be making history as she takes part in the finals of the beauty pageant in bangkok, thailand.
-
the pageant changed one of its longstanding policies in 2012, which stated that participants should be “naturally born” women.
-
angela hopes to highlight how misunderstood the transgender community is, and she also intends to send a message to #donaldtrump.
-
she particularly wants to raise awareness about the high rates of suicide within the community, and said: “who hasn’t suffered from prejudice? who hasn’t had to deal with bullying?”
-
the timing of her participation is particularly poignant, as a recent leaked white house document said trump’s administration is considering blocking transgender people from military service as well as changing the law to define gender by biological traits at birth.
-
angela responded to #trump, who used to own the miss universe competition, and said: “i always say: having a vagina didn’t transform me into a woman. i am a woman, already before birth, because my identity is here [her head.]”
-
she argued that the trans people being classified so narrowly on their gender is based on prejudice. “outsiders say what i can and cannot do, what i am and what i am not.
-
“no, i’m sorry. to be a woman is your identity. it doesn’t matter if you are white, black, if you have a vagina… if you have a penis.”
-
in spain, she works with a foundation that helps children struggling with the stigma of being trans.
-
“children are born without prejudices and i think that if we talk to them about diversity from a young age… we can create a new generation of human beings who are raised a lot better, more tolerant and respectful.”
-
critics say this year’s event is a pushback to stereotypes from the pre #metoo era, and is a time to promote inclusivity.
—
#diversity #equality #winning #loveislove #lgbt #marriageequality #empowerment #equalrights #lgbtq #fucktrump

text:
falta poco para el miss universo, donde nuestra sthefany gutierrez es una de las grandes favoritas.

vamos a desearle suerte y mentalizar la corona.

a pocas horas de celebrarse la edición número 67 del miss universe, que venevisión transmitirá en exclusiva a partir de las 8:00 pm este domingo 16 de diciembre, en vivo y directo desde bangkok, tailandia; crece la expectativa ante la posibilidad de que sthefany gutiérrez, miss venezuela 2017, obtenga la octava corona para venezuela. 
sthefany, quien portó la banda del estado delta amacuro en el miss venezuela 2017, ha deslumbrado desde su llegada a bangkok, no sólo con su belleza, sino también con la seguridad que transmite y su simpatía, que ha cautivado a todos los presentes. 
maría gabriela isler, directora de formación y relaciones públicas de la organización miss venezuela, se encuentra en bangkok desde hace algunos días para acompañar a sthefany durante el certamen, y para participar en las diferentes actividades que la organización prevé para los representantes de las franquicias. 
cabe resaltar que venezuela es el segundo país con más triunfos en el certamen de miss universo y lidera la lista de los países latinoamericanos con 7 coronas en su haber, ganadas por mujeres hermosas que son orgullo y ejemplo en el mundo: maritza sayalero (1979), irene sáez (1981), bárbara palacios (1986), alicia machado (1996), dayana mendoza (2008), y consecutivamente stefanía fernández (2009), logrando algo único en la historia del certamen, y maría gabriela isler (2013). además de la transmisión en vivo y en exclusiva por la señal de venevision, se puede seguir de cerca la participación de sthefany en www.missvenezuela.com, y a través de la etiqueta #sthefanyesvenezuela en las redes sociales oficiales del miss venezuela: @missvenezuela en instagram, missvenezuelaoficial en facebook y @missvzla en twitter. 
#missuniverse #metoo #me #woman 
#missvenezuela #miss #style #model #bangkok #mundo #movida #movidacaracas #movidavenezuela

to a sexual assault survivor, jessica jones was everything. after i saw jessica jones, i thought, that's me! people go through this too! other people are angry, other people can't talk about this, other people can't deal with this on their own! it's not just me! i got professionally diagnosed with ptsd after my assault. i started cbt. i'm not alone anymore. i had a name for what i survived. jessica jones will always be close to my heart in a way no other media can be. representation is so meaningful.

#jessicajones #metoo #marvel #representation

text:
i get this question a lot... "your gx is so tall, how does it handle on-road"? the answer: supringly well. i've put almost 1000 miles on this thing already since getting it back, and as i've gotten more comfortable driving it i've realized that it really is more stable than you'd think. why? well, unsprung weight is the biggest factor. yes, my truck has a lot of lift to fit the 40s, but i also added a ton (almost literally) of weight down low. these sd axles are 800lbs. each. each. and, i've got another 160+ lbs per corner in tires and wheels plus a much wider wheel track.

tl;dr: watch this video

text:
#barbietoo  before i left the house i made sure to dress in something loose that would not be too distracting. as i walk the streets of new york at night,one hand holds my groceries tightly, the other holds my pocket knife. i walk with urgency, my hoodie is up and my headphones in and,which are not playing music, act like a barrier between the men who catcalls and whistles at me. i see a masculine shadow at the end of the street, but i cannot see its owner. i fear it’s a man awaiting my passing. i make a detour and walk across the street. 
as i usually do on a weekend night, i was clubbing and hanging out with my girls. i normally go to gay clubs, but this weekend i went to a straight club.  once i felt a strong grip on my ass, i turned around to say what the hell, but this 6 foot tall frat guy in a polo would not look at me. this is the first time i  had my ass grabbed unsolicitedly. they have the balls to grab me, but they don’t own up to their actions. every 5 minutes i would take a headcount of my girls because the cocky boys would not listen to us when we said we did not want to grind with them. this was the first night where i saw that the boys were not listening to no. it made me wonder why they felt because it was dark and the music was loud that they could do what they want. i was not being listened to. “there is no greater threat to women than men? we’re the number one threat!” said louis c.k. in his hbo special. when are men taught to acknowledge boundaries? i should be able to leave and feel safe wherever i go without having to worry. i am tired with the way that men are treating me and other women. every women has there own story with harassment, but to tell mine i am using barbie as my proxy. when i was younger i looked up to her and she was a beacon of indepence and i vividly remember watching rapunzel barbie in my bubblegum pink room thinking “look at all that she can do for herself”. #photo #photography #art #camera #canon #fujifilm #fujitx1 #digital #digitalphoto #digitalphotography #digitalphotos #mirrorless #metoo #barbie #pink #hair #violent #ken #sexualassult

text:
what do fake friends, stress and fuck boys have in common?

control. ultimately we don’t believe we can be supported or nourished or loved enough by the universe or other people and so we arrange people and situations in our lives like  rearranging furniture in a room. 
lots of people can say, “you just need to learn how to receive” but for a survivor that can seem a threat.  being vulnerable is a threat.  opening your heart can be a threat. allowing yourself to financially thrive can be a threat. 
and so we keep arranging people like furniture, hoping it will eventually work out. 
and then one day it all changes.  the stress isn’t worth it.  you tire of the sub par men, the catty mean girl dynamic bores you. 
and you find someone to guide you on the path of healing.  and you glow. 
and then- life gets very interesting. 
join the glow self love club.  we’re getting jackets 😉
find me on fb or email- let’s glow 💚💕🦄🌈

text:
today after a separation of several years, i enjoyed a day in the city with my friend susie, who helped write this meme. . .
.
of course not all partnered people violate their partner’s boundaries, act in controlling ways, and criticize their partners’ interests and friends. but if you have done the agonizing work of exiting a toxic relationship, especially a toxic marriage, you often stop to appreciate those moments when it hits you afresh that you are your own person with your own plans, and nobody is holding you back anymore. have you left a toxic relationship? how did it feel when you started to recover?
•
•
•
[#imagedescription: a meme has a photo of two thirty-something women wearing eyeglasses and scarves on a city street. their expressions are assertive and determined. my caption below reads, “we don’t owe anyone an account of our time.” -divorcées in the wild]
.
.
.
.
